reviews.review: Loved it, family loved it, bad reviews are just bitter people

Ughhhhh. The movie may be enjoyable if you turn off your brain or if you just don't know anything about Star Wars. There was just too much in this movie; it should have been two movies. It looks like JJ was trying to correct things from The Last Jedi. Palpatine in the movie just made my head hurt. Rey has a ridiculous amount of power. I mean just ridiculous. And barely any actual Jedi training. The Force was used liberally as a way to a cheap plot device. The action scenes were mediocre. Especially that last space "battle." There were characters in there you just don't care about. Last minute backstories which just wasted time. Unanswered questions from previous movies and questions introduced in this movie. Questionable character/relationship development. Sigh.

Daisy Ridley did a great job. She's come a long way since Force Awakens. Adam Driver. Great of course. 

Overall, I think this is the worse movie from the sequel trilogy.

Clearly a reaction to the excrable TLJ, trying to cram three movie into one to make up for that mess. The movie zips around at lightspeed (pun intended) in typical JJ fashion to hide the fact that the 'story' is illogical and hollow, again in JJ fashion. At least he didn't have contempt for the franchise as Rian clearly did. Regardless, Lucasfilm should be ashamed for producing such a mess of a trilogy. Star Wars deserves better.

It was kinda boring and retconned things done in the previous film, every scene had a painful reminder that this was a Disney production and only so much could be done to save what the last Jedi started, of course the surprises in the movie were exciting but other than that the plot was kinda dumb and in no way do they explain some things so all you’re left to say to yourself is “oh okay I guess that’s what’s happening for no apparent reason other than because the film told me”
Loved the storyline. I wish the dialogue was a little better. Visually spectacular.

The worst peace of star wars I have ever seen, the story was an absolute horribly put together if there really was a story at all, every scene moved so far it was almost hard to keep up with it, definitely the most anticlimactic ending, overall if you haven't seen it don't waste your time and if you are a star wars fan I'm so sorry
Underwhelming. Still was fun, and a good film overall.
Action and effects were superb as always. Storyline was just ok....kind of predictable. Was good but probably the worst Star Wars of this series

This movie hurt ME, and I'm an adult. This was meant to be a kids movie, yet I saw kids being taken out of the theatre by their parents while they cried inconsolably. A tragic ending for a story about hope.

This movie gets back to what makes Star Wars great: the struggle between good and evil, fighting against the odds, triumph of the human. spirit, and awesome space and hand to hand combat, all while honoring the legacy of the franchise.

No political or SJW agenda promoted just simple  sci-fi pop culture fun.
